article.headline: Weber St. 72, Long Beach St. 63
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Kellen McCoy and Damian Lillard scored 15 points apiece and were among five Weber State players to score in double-figures as the Wildcats defeated Long Beach State 72-63 on Thursday night. Weber State (3-4) pulled away from the 49ers in the second half with a 20-6 run to take a 47-33 lead with 12:32 remaining in the game. Nick Hansen had nine of his 12 points during the stretch, all coming on 3-pointers. Daviin Davis had 14 points for WSU, and Kyle Bullinger finished with 10. Donovan Morris pulled Long Beach State (4-4) to within five points twice in the final 2:10, but the Wildcats made six free throws in the final 1:37 to seal the win. T.J. Robinson led the 49ers with 18 points and 10 rebounds, while Larry Anderson scored 15 and Morris finished with 14.
